sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K814005
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: All open reading frames contained within this part came from Anabaena variabilis ATCC 29413 genomic DNA (accession NC_007413.1).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Our research has focused on two novel biosynthetic pathways found in two distinct algal species. A pathway ending in the production of two UV-protective compounds, shinorine and mycosporine-glycine, was cloned from Anabaena varibalis. DHQS catalyzes the first step in the pathway, converting sedoheptulose-7-phosphate into dehydroquinate. Dehydroquinate-O-methyltransferase (O-MT) then generates 4-deoxygadusol, which is converted to mycosprine-glycine by ATP-grasp (ATPG). Finally, mycosporine-glycine is converted into shinorine by a non-ribosomal peptide synthase (NRPS).
This composite part contains protein generators for DHQS, O-MT, ATPG and the shinorine NRPS.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Genomic DNA was obtained from the Brett Barney Lab (University of Minnesota) for A. variabilis. From here, PCR primer extension was used to clone each individual gene (seven in total) with flanking restriction digest sites to be used for vector cloning. Each gene was cloned into an individual pUCBB BioBrick??? cloning vector containing a modified constitutive lac promoter (lacP')and RBS. From here, the resulting generators were stacked into a BioBrick??? vector using classical assembly techniques.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Nolan Kennedy, Michelle Goettge, Grayson Wawrzyn
